data.title: Sweden-based Christopher Mbamba earns maiden Harambee Stars call up
data.meta_description: Sweden-based Christopher Mbamba earns maiden Harambee Stars call up
data.text:
Sweden-based midfielder Christopher Mbamba has been named in Harambee Stars' 24-man provisional squad ahead of the Africa Cup of Nations Qualifying match against Ghana.

Goal exclusively reported that the Oskarshamns player was interested in representing his motherland at the senior level and FKF did not take chances when French coach Sebastien Migne gave him a call up on Thursday.

Mbamba was born to a Namibian father and Kenyan mother in Zimbabwe but moved to Sweden at a tender age and received his football education while there. He has since enjoyed stints in Norway at Ham Kam and English side Port Vale.

Article continues below

The 26-year old winger is among the new faces called to the squad alongside David Sesay, who plies his trade in England. Duke Abuya (Kariobangi Sharks) and Faruk Shikalo (Bandari), have also gotten the coach’s nod.

Coach Migné has further named an additional five man reserve squad as a precautionary measure, and they may be called upon to replace any of the 24 players in camp if need be.

The team is set to hit camp on March 17, 2019, in Nairobi ahead of the Ghana match which has been slated for March 23, 2019, in Accra.

Kenya provisional Squad: Goalkeepers: Patrick Matasi (St Georges, Ethiopia), Farouk Shikalo (Bandari) and John Oyemba (Kariobangi Sharks).

Defenders: Erick Ouma (Vasalund, Sweden), Musa Mohammed (Nkana FC, Zambia), David Owino (Zesco, Zambia), Brian Mandela (Maritzburg, South Africa), David Sesay (Crawley Town, England), Philemon Otieno (Gor Mahia, Kenya), Benard Ochieng (Vihiga United, Kenya), Joash Onyango (Gor Mahia, Kenya).

Midfielders: Erick Johanna (IF Brommapojkarna, Sweden), Johanna Omollo (Cercle Brugge, Belgium), Ismael Gonzales (UD Las Palmas B, Spain), Paul Were (Trikala, Greece), Victor Wanyama (Tottenham Hotspurs, England), Francis Kahata (Gor Mahia, Kenya), Christopher Tangen Mbamba (Oskarshamns, Sweden), Dennis Odhiambo (Sofapaka, Kenya), Anthony Akumu (Zesco, Zambia).

Forwards: Michael Olunga (Kashiwa Reysol, Japan), Duke Abuya (Kariobangi Sharks, Kenya), Cliff Nyakeya (Mathare United, Kenya), Masud Juma (Al Nasr, Libya).
